                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Twizlewink wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The Fountainhead by Ayn Rand - great read.
<br />

<br />
Also if you liked the Erdos biography (I'm assuming the mathamatician Erdos) I recommend picking up 'Godel, Escher, Bach: An Eternal Golden Braid' by Douglas Hoffstader. Note that Godel has two little dot thingies over the o so don't be confused. It's an amazing read and full of interesting and fun ideas. It's long so don't plan on getting through it in a day, or even a week. Personally I tackled it a bit at a time while reading something else, but it's broken down chapter by chapter so you don't miss much if anything by taking it slow.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
